# EEex Remote Console — Claude Code Context

Copy this to `CLAUDE.md` and customize for your setup.

## Project Overview

File-based IPC bridge for executing Lua inside a running BG:EE/BG2:EE game with EEex. Two files in the game's override directory serve as the communication channel: a command file (Lua source) and a result file (JSON).

## Key Files

- `eeexremote/M_EEexRC.lua` — in-game module (polls for commands, executes, writes JSON results)
- `eeexremote/EEexRC.menu` — invisible 1x1 menu element that fires `EEexRemote.Poll()` every render frame
- `tools/eeex-remote.sh` — bash CLI for sending commands
- `setup-eeexremote.tp2` — WeiDU installer

## Game Directory

Set this to your game's install path:

```
GAME_DIR=/path/to/Baldurs Gate II Enhanced Edition
OVERRIDE=$GAME_DIR/override
```

## Quick Test

```bash
tools/eeex-remote.sh "$OVERRIDE" 'print("hello")'
```

## Key References

- EEex source: https://github.com/Bubb13/EEex
- WeiDU documentation: https://weidu.org/
- IESDP (file format docs): https://gibberlings3.github.io/iesdp/

## EEex Gotchas

- `EEex_Menu_LoadFile("Name")` for .menu files, NOT `Infinity_DoFile`
- Each Lua `:gsub()` call must be on a separate statement (chaining passes count as arg)
- No `Infinity_DisplayString()` at M_ load time — engine display not ready
- `print()` output goes to EEex console, use `Infinity_DisplayString()` for in-game display
